# Install-time defense (SUPPLY-CHAIN-SECURITY.md, threat: malicious install scripts).
# Installs skip lifecycle (pre/post)install scripts by default. New transitive
# packages that genuinely need a script are surfaced by the install-hook gate
# (scripts/audit-install-hooks.mjs) and reviewed via .supply-chain/install-hooks.allowlist.
# A package that needs its native-binary postinstall to build locally can be run
# once with `yarn install --ignore-scripts false` (narrow exception, not the default).
--install.ignore-scripts true
